			Orb of Mastery Quest<br>
 <br>
<br>
<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
 <br>
<br>
Congratulations to Norseh of Guild Reconstructed from E'ci Server for being the first Mage to obtain The Orb of Mastery and for providing me with the screenshots of the Orb of Mastery.<br>
<br>
 <br>
<br>
IMPORTANT Kihun Solstin is the "final" quest NPC do not hand in you items for the Element of Air until you are ready to go to the Plane of Sky and turn in all four components to The Master of Elements to obtain the Orb of Mastery.<br>
<br>
 <br>
<br>
<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
 <br>
<br>
Lake Rathtear<br>
<br>
Your Location is 967.70, -665.27<br>
<br>
You say, 'hail Rykas'<br>
<br>
Rykas says 'Greetings Ronaldor , I am Rykas, chronicler of knowledge. I have journeyed all throughout the lands of Norrath, and I have learned many tales of adventure from people I have encountered during my travels. I have learned of legends known and unknown to most mortals. Are you in search of knowledge? <br>
You say, 'I am in search of knowledge'<br>
<br>
Rykas says 'A small task is needed if you wish to learn more. Do you wish to learn the tale of Magi'kot? <br>
<br>
You say, 'I wish to learn of the tale of Magi'kot'<br>
<br>
Rykas says 'If you seek to learn the tale of Trilith Magi'kot, your journey shall begin in the Commonlands. Search for Jahsohn Ak'sot and give him this token. He will share some of the knowledge I have bestowed upon him, and point you further down your path to Mastery. Bring me the Words of Mastery, Power of the Elements, and the Words of Magi'kot....Then you shall learn more about the power of the orb. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Rykas gives you a Token of Mastery take this to Jahsohn Aksot in the Western Commonlands.<br>
<br>
Western Commonlands<br>
<br>
Your Location is 62.78, 3639.68<br>
<br>
He will walk between these two locations.<br>
<br>
Your Location is 957.12, 3470.47<br>
<br>
Use the spell Sense Summoned to lead you to Jahsohn Aksot's pet.<br>
<br>
You say, 'hail Jahsohn Aksot'<br>
<br>
Jahsohn Aksot says 'Greetings, Ronaldor . <br>
<br>
Jahsohn Aksot says 'What is this? I cannot believe you found it! Where did you get this? <br>
<br>
You gain experience!!<br>
<br>
You say, 'Rykas gave it to me.'<br>
<br>
Jahsohn Aksot says 'I have not heard of anyone speaking that name out loud in years. Rykas once shared a tale with me, though I have lived with fear in my mind ever since. He told me afterwards that I did not have the balance I thought I had. Have you come for the Words of Magi'kot? <br>
<br>
You say, 'Yes I have come for the words of Magi'kot.'<br>
<br>
Jahsohn Aksot says 'The Words of Magi'kot can only be shared with those elementalists whose minds are of balance. The Words were separated into three pieces by a high council of Magi who feared that the story would bring an end to elementalists throughout Norrath. If you feel you wish to read from the sacred Power of the Orb then an elementalis of such power should easily accomplish this task. <br>
<br>
You say, 'What task.'<br>
